            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>Drag-to-group now actually works.</strong> Column headers with <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Groupable="true"</code> are HTML5-draggable whenever <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">ShowGroupPanel="true"</code> on the grid — independent of <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Reorderable</code>. The panel now has full <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">@@ondragover</code> / <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">@@ondrop</code> handlers and lights up <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">border-primary bg-primary/10</code> when a valid Groupable column is dragged over it. Drops on non-Groupable columns (or columns already grouped) are rejected silently.</li>
