        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">DataGrid — three virtualisation modes, all wired up</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>Virtualised server mode (NEW)</strong> — set
                    <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Virtualized="true"</code> +
                    <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">OnRangeRequest</code> and the grid
                    fetches a sliding window of rows from your backend as the user scrolls (Blazor's
                    <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;Virtualize ItemsProvider&gt;</code>).
                    Pagination is hidden automatically; sort, column filter, and global search all trigger
                    <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">RefreshDataAsync()</code> so the next
                    request reflects the new query state. Public
                    <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">grid.RefreshVirtualizedAsync()</code>
                    for manual refetch after external mutations.</li>
                <li><strong>Virtualised client mode (correctness fix)</strong> — the in-memory virtualiser now passes
                    <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">SpacerElement="tr"</code>.
                    Without it, Blazor's default <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;div&gt;</code>
                    spacers are invalid <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;tbody&gt;</code> children
                    and the browser hoisted them out of the table, breaking layout whenever the threshold tripped.</li>
                <li><strong>New tunables</strong>:
                    <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">VirtualItemSize</code> (row-height estimate, default 41 px) and
                    <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">VirtualOverscanCount</code> (default 3 rows).</li>
                <li><strong>PageSizeOptions</strong> — configurable rows-per-page selector (default
                    <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">[10, 25, 50, 100]</code>);
                    pass <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">new[] { 10, 50, 100, 200, 300 }</code>
                    for larger datasets, or empty array to hide the selector entirely.</li>
